The paper deals with a signal processing problem of recovering a superposition of point sources using bandlimited measurements, which is a common problem in imaging. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the desire for the algorithm to run quickly, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of Fourier measurements and concentration bounds for sampling suggests that the paper may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
